      "text": "The question whether communication between computers and humans is possible, useful or even \"human\" is wrongly posed according to the understanding of systems theory (Fuchs, 1991). Since communication is formed only as an autopoietic product by communication itself and social systems achieve closure in this way, there can be no communication with computers."
